o bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Pilate was born about 1248, in Ireland. She had at least 3 sons with Andrew de Cusack Lord of Gerrardstown."},"et":{"abt 1248–":"umbes 1248–Surnud","1248–1295":"1248–1295","1271–1346":"1271–1346","1273–Male":"1273–Surnud","1275–1334":"1275–1334","1248–Female":"1248–Surnud","abt 1248":"umbes 1248","1248":"1248","1346":"1346","1334":"1334","1275":"1275","1273":"1273","1295":"1295","1271":"1271","about 1275":"umbes 1275","about 1273":"umbes 1273","of, Geradstown, Meath, Ireland":"County Meath, Iirimaa","Gerrardstown, County Meath, Ireland":"Gerrardstown, County Meath, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Geradstown, Meath, Ireland":"County Meath, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"abt 1248–":"noin 1248–Kuollut","1248–1295":"1248–1295","1271–1346":"1271–1346","1273–Male":"1273–Kuollut","1275–1334":"1275–1334","1248–Female":"1248–Kuollut","abt 1248":"noin 1248","1248":"1248","1346":"1346","1334":"1334","1275":"1275","1273":"1273","1295":"1295","1271":"1271","about 1275":"noin 1275","about 1273":"noin 1273","of, Geradstown, Meath, Ireland":"County Meath, Irlanti","Gerrardstown, County Meath, Ireland":"Gerrardstown, County Meath, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti",